The paper discusses a search system for web archives, which involves information retrieval (IR) techniques and natural language processing (NLP) for query auto-completion and related query suggestion. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also deals with web archiving, which falls under the category of digital libraries (cs.DL). Additionally, the paper mentions entity-oriented search, which is a subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses user feedback and user-friendly interfaces, which are relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.CY). Finally, the paper mentions the challenges of dealing with large-scale web archive collections, which is relevant to computer networks and communications (cs.CR).
